					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2356296#post-2885976</guid>
				<title>Relax, it&#039;s a listusers module that displays the username of whoever&#039;s reading it.</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2356296/scp-tldr-j#post-2885976</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 22 Jun 2017 03:28:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Communism will win</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>617958</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thanks to everyone who gave suggestions for this, don't remember who they were. Feel free to claim credit if you like.</p> <p>Form L is a listpages module that selects the longest SCP that's rated under +35, and Form N uses a really clunky tag-based listpages module to grab a live rating of the Bright list.</p> <p><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3039">SCP-3039</a> is great, and unlike this article, it is NOT tl;dr. You should read it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
